        <name>38.1.1.4 Basic Continuous Probability</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let \(X\) be a random variable and consider its pdf in the figure below.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/38.1%20figure%208.svg" alt="Graph of a function where: the line y=0 everywhere except for two line segments - one from (-2,0) to (0,1/2), and the second one from (0,1/2) to (2,0)." width="378" height="159" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Calculate the probability that \(X\) takes on a value between \(\displaystyle{@-1/a@}\) and \(\displaystyle{@1/a@}\).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\(P\left(\displaystyle{{@-1/a@}} \leq X \leq \displaystyle{{@1/a@}}\right)\) = [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol class="HELM_parts_inline"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;h4 class="HELM_solution"&gt;Solution&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;First, we write down the pdf:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;"&gt;\[f(x) = \left\{\begin{array}{ll}0, &amp;amp; \text{if $x \leq -2$}, \\ \dfrac{1}{2} + \dfrac{x}{4}, &amp;amp; \text{if $-2 \leq x \leq 0$},\\ \dfrac{1}{2} - \dfrac{x}{4}, &amp;amp; \text{if $0 \leq x \leq 2$},\\ 0, &amp;amp; \text{if $x \geq 2$}.\end{array}\right.\]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;"&gt;Then, we see that&amp;nbsp;\(\text{P}({{@-1/a@}} \leq X \leq {{@1/a@}})=\int_{{{@-1/a@}}}^{{{@1/a@}}} f(x) \; dx.\) Since \(f(x)\) is an even function, we have that&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\[\begin{align*} \text{P}({{@-1/a@}} \leq X \leq {{@1/a@}})&amp;amp;=2\int_{0}^{{@1/a@}} f(x) \; dx\\ &amp;amp; = 2 \int_{0}^{{{@1/a@}}} \dfrac{1}{2} - \dfrac{x}{4} \; dx\\ &amp;amp; = 2\left(\left.\dfrac{x}{2}\right|_{0}^{{{@1/a@}}} - \left.\dfrac{x^2}{8}\right|_{0}^{{{@1/a@}}}\right) \\&amp;amp;= 2\left({{@1/(2*a)@}}-{{@1/(8*a^2)@}}\right)\\ &amp;amp; = {{@ta1@}}. \end{align*}\]&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
